-- Asian Terminals, Jollibee, San Miguel: Philippine Stocks Preview
-- B y   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 2011-12-27T01:16:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/asian-terminals-jollibee-san-miguel-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual (PCOMP)  moves in  Philippine (PASHR)  trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.3 percent to
4,387.06.  Abacus Consolidated Resources & Holdings Inc. (ABA)  : The
company will have a “banner year” in 2012 based on the revenue
prospects of its mining and property projects, a stock exchange
filing showed, citing President Leonardo Gayao. The stock was
unchanged at 91 centavos.  Metro Pacific Tollways Corp. (TOL)  : The nation’s biggest
toll-road operator said a subsidiary obtained a one billion peso
loan to fund its 2012 expansion, a stock exchange filing showed.
The stock advanced 3.8 percent to 8.30 pesos.  Metro Pacific
Investments Corp. (MPI)  (MPI), parent of Metro Pacific Tollways, rose
1.3 percent to 3.62 pesos.  PAL Holdings Inc. (PAL)  : Philippine Airlines Inc., the
nation’s largest carrier and a unit of the company, stopped
direct flights to New Delhi due to weak demand and will instead
divert the flights first to Bangkok so it can pick up passengers
before proceeding to India’s capital, Philippine Daily Inquirer
reported, citing Philippine Air President Jaime Bautista. The
stock rose 0.7 percent to 6.02 pesos.  San Miguel Corp. (SMC)  : The largest Philippine food and
drinks company will hold on to the shares in Rockwell Land Corp.
that it will get as dividends, BusinessWorld reported, citing
 San Miguel  Vice Chairman Ramon Ang. The stock increased 0.8
percent to 117.90 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
